Vault manager install

Install a single-node Vault service managed by this tool.

Usage:
  ${VAULT_MANAGER_CMD} install [VERSION] [options]
  ${VAULT_MANAGER_CMD} install [--version <VERSION>] [options]

Options:
  --version <VERSION>        Vault version. Default resolves latest, then falls back to ${DEFAULT_VAULT_VERSION}.
  --listen-address <ADDR>    Listener address, default: 0.0.0.0:8200
  --cluster-address <ADDR>   Listener cluster address, default: 0.0.0.0:8201
  --api-addr <URL>           Vault api_addr, default: ${DEFAULT_VAULT_ADDR}
  --cluster-addr <URL>       Vault cluster_addr, default: http://127.0.0.1:8201
  --no-tls                   Disable listener TLS, default
  --tls-auto                 Enable TLS and auto-generate a certificate
  --tls-cert-file <FILE>     Listener TLS certificate file
  --tls-key-file <FILE>      Listener TLS key file
  --tls-ca-cert-file <FILE>  CA certificate used by client checks
  --tls-dns <NAME>           Add DNS SAN for --tls-auto
  --tls-ip <IP>              Add IP SAN for --tls-auto
  --tls-common-name <NAME>   Certificate common name for --tls-auto, default: vault-server

TLS modes:
  Default and --no-tls disable listener TLS.
  --tls-auto generates a CA and server certificate under ${TLS_DIR}.
  --tls-cert-file and --tls-key-file use your existing certificate pair.
